>>__ Parse.temp_set_grammars $ valOf $ grammarDB {thyname="hol"};
## `UNCURRY_EXISTS_CONV`

``` hol4
PairRules.UNCURRY_EXISTS_CONV : conv
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Uncurrys consecutive existential quantifications into a paired
existential quantification.

### Example

``` hol4
>>__ load "PairRules";

>> PairRules.UNCURRY_EXISTS_CONV (Term `?x y. x + y = y + x`);

>> PairRules.UNCURRY_EXISTS_CONV (Term `?(w,x) (y,z). w+x+y+z = z+y+x+w`);
```

### Failure

`UNCURRY_EXISTS_CONV tm` fails if `tm` is not a consecutive existential
quantification.

